  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-001">.NET 8 Minimal API + BackgroundService. Dispatch runs in-proc.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-008">Authorization happens at the calling endpoint (endpoint-filter). This dispatch layer enforces phase boundaries — a different axis from auth. Both apply.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">DI minimalism. `IToolHandlerRegistry` registered once via `AddActionEngineModule()`. Tool handlers registered via the registry's `Register&lt;THandler&gt;(resourceId)` method, not by individual DI registrations.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">PublicContracts boundary. `IToolHandlerRegistry` is internal — NOT exposed via the facade. Phase 4 `IActionEngineFacade.RunAction()` is the CRUD-side surface; it internally calls the registry.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-015">Audit Tier 2 + Tier 3: every dispatch (successful AND denied) MUST write audit. Tier 2 hashes the dispatch envelope; Tier 3 Cosmos work history records the dispatch outcome (including phase-denied outcomes for security forensics).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-019">`PhaseToolDeniedException` propagates to caller; caller (task 024 / task 040) translates to ProblemDetails or `ResourceExecutionResult.Failed` per surface.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">No new NuGet packages.</constraint>
    <constraint source="bff-extensions.md">Pre-merge: placement (in BFF — dispatch is core AE machinery, never CRUD-side). Zero publish-size delta.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">LAVERN Pattern #8 (referenced in design.md §5, §11): mechanical phase enforcement at `IToolHandlerRegistry` dispatch. NOT prompt-coached. The Builder Agent's prompt CANNOT circumvent it because the registry is the only dispatch path.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Spec gate G4: `IToolHandlerRegistry` Phase deny-tools throws `PhaseToolDeniedException` — verified by `PhaseDeniedTools` integration test (task 063).</constraint>
  </constraints>

