  <steps>
    <step order="0">Context check: confirm baseline build passes; task 020 merged or branch-loadable; LAVERN Pattern #8 reading complete (`lavern-pattern-assessment.md` + design.md §5).</step>
    <step order="1">Read all files in `&lt;knowledge&gt;&lt;files&gt;`. Pay close attention to design.md §5 (Phase deny-tools subsection), design.md §11 (LAVERN cross-references), and `lavern-pattern-assessment.md` (external reference for pattern intent).</step>
    <step order="2">Sketch the interface:
      - `IToolHandlerRegistry.DispatchAsync(string resourceId, Dictionary&lt;string, object&gt; parameters, IPhaseContext phaseContext)` returns `Task&lt;ToolDispatchResult&gt;`.
      - `IToolHandlerRegistry.Register&lt;THandler&gt;(string resourceId) where THandler : IToolHandler` — handler registration entry point used by `AddActionEngineModule()`.
      - `IPhaseContext.CurrentPhase` (enum: `Authoring`, `Execution`, plus `Unknown` for sessions without an explicit phase).
      - `PhaseToolDeniedException(string resourceId, string phase, string denyReason)`.</step>
    <step order="3">Implement `PhaseToolDeniedException.cs`: extends `Exception`, properties `ResourceId`, `Phase`, `DenyReason`. Message format: `"Tool '{ResourceId}' is denied in phase '{Phase}'. Deny rule: {DenyReason}."` Add `[Serializable]` if needed for cross-AppDomain (likely not in MVP).</step>
    <step order="4">Implement `IPhaseContext.cs` + a default `PhaseContext.cs` implementation. Phase enum: `Authoring`, `Execution`, `Unknown`. Where the context comes from depends on the caller — chat-session callers pass `sprk_aichatcontextmap.currentPhase`; Action runtime endpoint passes `Execution` directly.</step>
    <step order="5">Implement `ToolHandlerRegistry.cs`:
      - In-memory dictionary `Dictionary&lt;string, Type&gt; _handlers` (resourceId → handler type).
      - `Register&lt;THandler&gt;(resourceId)` adds to dictionary.
      - `DispatchAsync`:
        1. Look up handler type by `resourceId`; throw `KeyNotFoundException` if not found (caller translates to NotFound).
        2. Read Tool Registry entry for `resourceId` (via injected Dataverse client or cached lookup).
        3. Check `entry.PhaseRestrictions` for `phaseContext.CurrentPhase`; if `resourceId` is in the deny list, throw `PhaseToolDeniedException` with the deny reason from the registry.
        4. Resolve the handler instance from DI (`IServiceProvider.GetRequiredService(handlerType)`).
        5. Invoke `handler.InvokeAsync(parameters)`.
        6. Return `ToolDispatchResult { Status = Succeeded, Payload, LatencyMs }`.</step>
    <step order="6">Wire ADR-015 audit: every dispatch path (success, phase-denied, exception) writes a Tier 2 hash event + Tier 3 Cosmos work history record. The phase-denied path is critical for security forensics — confirm middleware picks it up via exception filter OR add explicit audit write in the catch block.</step>
    <step order="7">Register `IToolHandlerRegistry` (singleton) in `AddActionEngineModule()`. Tool handlers are registered via `registry.Register&lt;Handler&gt;(resourceId)` calls inside the module — these count toward ADR-010 ≤15 budget only as the registry itself (singletons under the registry don't count individually).</step>
    <step order="8">Write unit tests at `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/ActionEngine/Dispatch/ToolHandlerRegistryTests.cs`:
      - (a) Handler dispatches successfully when no phase restriction applies.
      - (b) Handler dispatches successfully when phase is allowed.
      - (c) `PhaseToolDeniedException` thrown when dispatching `SendEmail` in `Authoring` phase (given Tool Registry mock with `PhaseRestrictions.Authoring.DenyTools = [SendEmail]`).
      - (d) `PhaseToolDeniedException` thrown when dispatching `CreateActionTemplate` in `Execution` phase.
      - (e) Exception message includes resource id + phase + deny reason.
      - (f) Audit middleware receives a Tier 2 event for the denied dispatch (verified via `IAuditWriter` mock).
      - (g) Unknown phase + Tool with PhaseRestrictions → dispatches (fail-open for `Unknown` is the safer Phase 2 default; document in code comments + escalate if owner wants fail-closed).</step>
    <step order="9">Verify build + tests + format: `dotnet build`, `dotnet test --filter "ToolHandlerRegistry"`, `dotnet format`. Verify NFR-10.</step>
    <step order="9.5">Run quality gates: `code-review` on the new files (security-sensitive — request thorough review); `adr-check` verifies ADR-008 (auth orthogonal layer respected), ADR-010 (DI budget), ADR-013 (NOT exposed via PublicContracts), ADR-015 (audit on all dispatch paths including denied), ADR-019 (typed exception propagates cleanly), ADR-029 (no new packages).</step>
    <step order="10">Update `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: mark task 026 ✅. Update `current-task.md`. Note the `Unknown` phase fail-open decision for owner awareness (escalate if owner wants fail-closed default).</step>
    <step order="11">Document the LAVERN Pattern #8 enforcement contract in `projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/notes/handoffs/` — including the `Unknown` phase semantics, the exception envelope, and how task 024 (`InvokeResourceTool`) consumes the typed exception. Commit with brief recap.</step>
  </steps>

