  <notes>
    LAVERN Pattern #8 is the canonical security boundary for this project. Code review should treat this task with the rigor of a security-sensitive change. The mechanical-not-prompt-coached property is what gives the Builder Agent (Phase 5+) safety guarantees — if a Builder Agent prompt instructs the LLM to "ignore phase restrictions," the registry's enforcement still wins because the dispatch path is unconditional.

    `Unknown` phase fail-open is a deliberate Phase 2 default — sessions without an explicit phase context (e.g., legacy chat sessions before `sprk_aichatcontextmap.currentPhase` is populated) dispatch normally. If the owner wants fail-closed (deny unless phase explicitly allowed), escalate before committing. Phase 5 work seeds `currentPhase` for all new sessions.

    The audit on phase-denied dispatch is non-trivial security forensics. ADR-015 middleware should pick up the thrown exception via existing exception-filter wiring, but VERIFY this in test (f) — add an explicit `_auditWriter.WriteDeniedDispatch(...)` call in the catch block if the middleware doesn't auto-fire on typed exceptions.

    The interface `IToolHandlerRegistry` may already exist as a stub from task 014 (BFF module skeleton). This task fills in the dispatch logic + phase enforcement; do NOT re-create the interface if 014 already shipped it.
  </notes>

